name: Kevin Townsend
bio: STC/Toronto water link, affordable housing and active transportation. City Councillor for St. Catharines

social_posts.post_text: A few weeks back we officially were sworn in to begin our new term of council. I look forward to continuing to work for you St. Catharines! #ourhomestc #niagara
What a year 2022 was! I want to wish you all a Happy New Year and fun filled 2023. #happynewyear #goodbye2022 #happy2023
Finally, a reunion years in the making! Great to see the old crew and catch up on life. #grandcayman
What a great game last night! @buffalosabres win and Devin Levi gets his first ever career NHL win!
What a small world! It was so awesome to run into my former council colleague Councillor @lori_littleton1 in #cancun! It was great to catch up and chat about life outside of politics.
Ran into my childhood hero tonight - totally surreal! Who knew a casual night out could turn into such a cool memory?  #bretthart #canadianicon #wwe #champion

Delighted to share that the motion I proposed at Monday's council meeting passed! Together, we're making strides toward more affordable housing in St. Catharines. Thanks to everyone for their support - let's keep pushing for progress. #CityCouncil  #AffordableHousing #ProgressMade

Had a great day golfing in this years Mayor’s Golf Tournament! Mayor @matsiscoe will use the funds raised to support local groups in need of support including Niagara Children’s Centre and Niagara Health Foundation. #charitygolf #golf #ourhomestc

Today at #AMO2023 we met with Minister @stanchompp to discuss the water link between St. Catharines and Toronto. Thank you minister for listening and for your support on this game-changing project for Niagara.

Thank you  to Minister @davidpiccini for taking time today to listen to our concerns around our needs for more support with linear infrastructure and better coordination for community emergency response. #AMO2023

St. Catharines delegation at the Association of Municipalities of Ontario (AMO) Conference has wrapped up a series of meetings with provincial ministers and officials to help keep the City’s strategic priorities front and centre.
🗞️ Read the full release: https://tinyurl.com/ycx8ts69

I’m thrilled to be partaking in the expert forum on climate change at the @unitednations. Climate change has impacted many cities around the world, we must come together to analyze the data, share solutions, and repair the damage to help protect our planet. #climatechange #savetheplanet
December 1973 Tolls were removed from the Garden City Skyway!
